The paper discusses a web-based application that uses statistical models (Bayesian multilevel logistic regression) to estimate institutional networks based on papers published between 2007 and 2011. The application focuses on scientific institutions worldwide and investigates collaboration success within Scopus subject areas. Given the focus on scientific institutions and collaboration success, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the "best paper rate" as an indicator for evaluating collaboration success, which suggests relevance to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of statistical models also suggests relevance to cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.DB (Databases).
